Source: tas-agent
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: TAS <tas@tee-attestation.dev>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 12), cargo, rustc, pkg-config, libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.0

Package: tas-agent
Architecture: amd64
Depends: systemd, cryptsetup, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: tas-agent-dracut | tas-agent-initramfs
Description: TEE Attestation Service Agent
 Agent for fetching LUKS encryption keys from the TEE Attestation Service
 using hardware-based TEE attestation (AMD SEV-SNP, Intel TDX).
 Integrates with systemd ask-password for automatic LUKS volume unlock
 during boot, with TTY fallback on failure.

Package: tas-agent-initramfs
Architecture: all
Depends: tas-agent, initramfs-tools, cryptsetup-initramfs, ${misc:Depends}
Description: TAS Agent initramfs-tools integration
 Hooks and scripts for integrating TAS Agent into initramfs-tools based
 initrd images for automatic LUKS unlock during early boot.
 .
 Note: SEV-SNP/TDX attestation requires the sev-guest or tdx-guest kernel
 modules, which are shipped in the linux-modules-extra package. Install
 linux-modules-extra for your kernel version if not already present.

Package: tas-agent-dracut
Architecture: all
Depends: tas-agent, dracut, dracut-network, ${misc:Depends}
Description: TAS Agent dracut integration
 Dracut module for integrating TAS Agent into dracut-based initrd images
 for automatic LUKS unlock during early boot.
